# Allowed-strings list for git-secrets.
#
# These regexes describe SYNTHETIC test fixtures that look like provider keys
# but are not real secrets. Anything matched here is exempted from the
# git-secrets pre-commit hook.
#
# Real keys live ONLY in:
#   - the gitignored .env file
#   - pass(1)
#   - macOS keychain (Claude Code subscription auth)
#
# If a real key ever lands in the diff: STOP, revoke the key, do not bypass
# this hook. The patterns below are tight enough that real keys won't match.

# Predictable alphabetical / repeating fake suffixes used in tests.
sk-or-v1-abcdef[0-9a-z]+
sk-or-v1-abcdefghijklmnop
1234567890:AAHwIUabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz12
